# Keep the Docker build context small + the build hermetic.
#
# The CLI image builds `-p dreggnet-cli`, whose dependency closure is
# control → bridge → durable → exec (owned wasmi sandbox). Cargo still needs
# every workspace member's Cargo.toml to resolve the workspace, so the `net/`
# sources stay in the context, but the giant build artifacts and VCS metadata do
# not need to ship to the daemon.

# Build artifacts (the root target/ alone is tens of GB).
target/
**/target/

# VCS + editor cruft.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitmodules
**/*.rs.bk
.DS_Store

# Secrets + local env.
.env
secrets/
*.log

# cbindgen output written into a crate dir by net/base/build.rs.
net/base/libelidebase.h

# Don't recurse the docker inputs into themselves.
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
.dockerignore
